article_title: Alibaba launches new open-source AI model for 'cost-effective AI agents'
summary: Alibaba Cloud has launched a new multimodal AI model, "Qwen2.5-Omni-7B," that can process various inputs and generate real-time text and speech responses. The model is open-sourced on platforms like Hugging Face and Github, aiming to develop cost-effective AI agents, especially for intelligent voice applications. Alibaba and other Chinese tech giants have been rapidly releasing new AI models amid the country's AI fervor. Alibaba recently announced plans to invest $53 billion in cloud computing and AI infrastructure over the next three years. The company has also secured partnerships with Apple for AI integration in iPhones and with BMW for integration into next-generation intelligent vehicles.
